race.comment: BIANCELLI (7) has her unbeaten record tarnished first up at Cranbourne but her reputation certainly didn't take a hit, just settling a length further back than was ideal on the fast deck, taking a lot of ground off the winner late to be beaten a long neck. The stable suggested she'd improve for the run there and if she does, she should take a power of beating. CELERITY (16) was just behind BIANCELLI at Cranbourne and did start shorter than her in the market. She gets in slightly better at the weights here although did have a better run in transit. MANOLO BLING (5) stuck on fairly fresh in Listed company at Flemington which reads well. She's a speedy sort who can make use of the 3kg claim and be in this for a long way. SWEETHEARTED (6) has been solid to the line in two runs this time in, back to 1000m may be a bit sticky but she has claims. RIPROAR (8) might need further but has the ability for the new yard.
